H0.text: Food chain is the further subdivision of a food web that usually has a few links in it.

H1.text: The food pyramid is the subdivision into which a food web can be broken up, typically containing a few links.

H2.text: Oxygen chain is the subdivision of a food web that usually has a few links in it.

H3.text: Water chain is the further subdivision of a food web that usually has a few links in it.

A4.text: A food chain is a linear network of links in a food web.

A5.text: There are usually no more than five tropic levels in a food chain.
